claim: Recombinant technology leads to a broader immune response that may provide cross-protection, even in a mismatch season.
explanation: A comparative table of baseline characteristics and influenza case rates by vaccine type (RIV4 vs SD-IIV4 in 18–64 year olds; SD-IIV4, RIV4, and RIV4+HD-IIV4+Adj-IIV in ≥65 year olds) across two influenza seasons (2018–2019 and 2019–2020), showing n (%) and P-values for demographic factors, season distribution, influenza cases, and high-risk conditions. The table presents demographic characteristics and crude influenza case rates by vaccine group, but contains no data on immune response breadth, cross-protection, or mismatch season performance by recombinant vaccine versus other platforms, so it does not support the claim. Note: Analysis limited to visible table data; no immunogenicity or strain-specific mismatch information provided.
